            <p>We commit ourselves to the fair evaluation (assessment) of achievement in this course.  Formative evaluation (assessment) is made by placing an emphasis on the usual learning process.<br>
The evaluation (assessment) of achievement is based on the assignments given in each of four units and on attendance.  You are required to write these evaluations(assessments) on special sheets. <br> 
Typographical errors and omissions will result in the deduction of points.  If an assignment is late, one point is deducted per day. </p>

            <br> 
            <p>First unit: "How do human beings learn? - From high school to university to members of society" (3 points)<br>
            Assignment: "Five keys to studying to pass down to younger students." (800 characters)</p>
            
            <p>Second unit: "What exactly is Nagoya University? - Nagoya University viewed from data" (3 points)<br>
            Assignment: List three "requests to Nagoya University as an educational institution." (800 characters)</p>
            
            <p>Third unit: "What is the presence of Nagoya University students' like? - focusing on the students' attitudes toward learning" (3 points)<br>
            Assignment to be accomplished: Prepare a report on "What I want to study at Nagoya University". (800 characters)</p>
            
            <p>Fourth unit: "Development of individuality by Nagoya University students - how to develop yourself" (5 points)<br>
            Assignment: "Compile your thoughts regarding how to lead a fruitful life in college." (1,200 characters)</p>
            <br>
            
            <p>Students' attendance is confirmed on the basis of commentaries they are required to write during the last ten minutes of every class (starting with the second class).<br>
            Attendance points are set as follows by the point-plus method:<br>
            Absent from only two classes throughout the semester: plus 2 points; absent from only one class: plus 4 points; prize for perfect attendance: plus 6 points.<br>
            Hence, with 14 points for the assignments plus 6 points for perfect attendance, the maximum number of points is 20.</p>
